## Rules
- Base your conclusion ONLY on the identified states and KB definitions above.
{% if framework == "mbti" %}
- CRITICAL: The "type" field MUST equal the concatenation of the four dimension labels in order IE→SN→TF→JP. Example: if IE=E, SN=N, TF=T, JP=P, then type="ENTP".
- Each dimension label must be a single letter from its pair: IE∈{I,E}, SN∈{S,N}, TF∈{T,F}, JP∈{J,P}.
{% else %}
- Each trait label must be exactly "HIGH" or "LOW" (uppercase).
{% endif %}
- If states conflict, choose the majority signal and note the ambiguity in `explanation`.
- Every dimension/trait must cite at least one supporting state index.
- Do NOT copy the placeholder values from the schema. Fill them with real values from YOUR analysis.
- Return valid JSON only. No markdown, no commentary outside the JSON.
